- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel approach to support the survival selection process in multi-objective evolutionary algorithms with surrogate models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves the use of surrogate models to improve the performance of evolutionary algorithms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to build surrogate models. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve parallelization of the evolutionary algorithm. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve the development of software tools for implementing the proposed approach.
